Implemented Conway's Game of Life with sparse representation in `src/game-of-life.ts` and tests in `src/game-of-life.spec.ts`. All 10 tests pass, TypeScript compiles cleanly.

Key design choices:
- Uses `Map<string, number>` to count neighbor contributions, iterating only over living cells and their neighborhoods (sparse).
- Encodes coordinates as `"x,y"` strings for Set/Map keys, supporting negative coordinates.
- Applies B3/S23 rules: count==3 (birth or survival) or count==2 with cell currently alive (survival).
